== Noun ==
* A person who professes beliefs and opinions that he or she does not hold

== Adjective ==
* Fraudulent; having a misleading appearance

== Etymology ==
"not genuine," [[wikipedia:1900|1900]], phoney, perhaps an alteration of ''fawney'' "gilt brass ring used by swindlers" ([[wikipedia:1781|1781]]), from Ir. ''fainne'' "ring." The noun meaning "phony person or thing" is attested from [[wikipedia:1902|1902]].

